review_blob: Draft at a bar. Enticing aroma, spicy, nutmeg, cinnamon. Pours darker than I expect for the style. Taste is nice but a little sweeter than I expected. Not much carbonation. Overall draws you in at first and enjoyable, but I wouldnt drink several in a row.
Smoke, orange marmalade, licorice. Sweet and not very bitter. Good mouthfeel and interesting character. Nothing like any ESB Ive ever had before, although Im not very well versed in the style.
Caramel, bread, chocolate, coffee, roasty, leather, earthy, banana, raisin, soy sauce, vanilla
